About the PharmD Program













            One College, Two Campuses, Unlimited Opportunities
          Heading link



 
Copy link



            The UIC College of Pharmacy is located on two campuses: Chicago and Rockford. They are about 90 miles apart, but the campuses are constantly connected by the latest distance learning technology and a united mission to produce the next generation of pharmacy leaders. Students in both Chicago and Rockford receive the same education, have active student organizations, perform public service for their communities, have numerous research and residency opportunities, and receive the same degree upon graduation.
          





              Chicago Campus
            




              Rockford Campus
            




              Learn more about the One College, Two Campus model
            




